               <msContents>
                  <summary>Recto contains the bottom half of a commercial letter. The sender mentions a shipper called Sam'un. The sender also writes that he is in need of 'true velvet' ('you know, may God preserve you, my need for true velvet'). The letter ends with greetings to the adressee and several other individuals (Abu Ishaq, Abu Muhammad).</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Recto (perpendicular to fibres) contains 11 lines and 3 lines in the right margin. The original cutting lines are preserved at the bottom and on the right sides and partially at the top.</note>
                     <note type="general">Verso is blank.</note>
                     <note type="local_note">Held in the Special Collections Department of Bobst library of NYU and stored loose in acid-free file folders.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar-Arab">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
